The '''Petranaki arena''', also known as the '''Arena of Justice''' and commonly referred to as the '''Geonosian execution arena''', was brought about by both a need for entertainment in the rigid [[Geonosian/Legends|Geonosian]] society, and an efficient way of disposing of otherwise resource-draining prisoners. It was named after [[Petranaki/Legends|Petranaki]], a form of arena combat fighting that utilized several special weapons, including the [[Static pike/Legends|Picador's spear]]. The most popular attractions used deadly beasts in combat, resulting in the extinction of some of the more crowd-pleasing creatures on Geonosis.

Those looking to trade with [[Geonosis/Legends|Geonosis]] would often provide exotic predators for the arena entertainment as payment. Such creatures included [[Acklay/Legends|acklays]], [[Nexu/Legends|nexus]], [[Reek/Legends|reeks]], and [[Mongworst/Legends|mongworsts]].

The arena itself was a natural formation carved out by millennia of weathering, with additions made by the Geonosians. Its floor consisted of sand and silt upon which events took place. The lower walls of the arena base included ancient low-relief carvings depicting famous battles and events. The arena could also be flooded for aquatic events.

A large tunnel connected the arena to an underground Geonosian [[Geonosis droid factories/Legends|droid factory]] and was below the [[Geonosian High Audience Chamber]]. Droid storage chambers were also located nearby.

==History==
[[File:PetranakiArenaBattle-CGSWG.png|thumb|left|300px|The [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] fight off the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatists]] in the arena.]]
{{Quote|The felons before you have been convicted of espionage against the Sovereign System of Geonosis. Their sentence of death is to be carried out in this arena immediately!|translated=1|Sun Fac|<ref name="AotC novel">[[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones (novelization)|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'' novelization]]</ref>}}
Shortly before the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|First Battle of Geonosis]] and the outbreak of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]], and [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]] were all scheduled for execution, having been convicted of espionage by [[Poggle the Lesser/Legends|Poggle the Lesser]]. With a mix of ingenuity and [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] abilities, the trio evaded the beasts long enough for [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]] to arrive with a [[Jedi assault team/Legends|strike force]] of Jedi Knights. In response, large numbers of [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droids]] flooded the arena, signaling the start of the Clone Wars. Fighting soon erupted between the two sides.<ref name="Episode 2" /> The 102 Jedi<ref name="Note">[[Star Wars: Episode II — Attack of the Clones 4|''Star Wars: Episode II — Attack of the Clones'' 4]] states that 100 [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] of the [[Jedi assault team/Legends|Geonosis strike team]] participated in the arena battle. [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']] shows that [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] also fought in the battle until [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]]'s arrival, bringing the total number to 102.</ref> were overwhelmed by the sheer amounts of droids, and soon<ref name="Episode 2" /> only just over 20 of them survived.<ref name="AotC novel" /> A dozen Jedi formed a circle. It would have been a defeat for the Jedi if not for the timely arrival of Master [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] and the newly christened [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]], who managed to rout the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]] forces.<ref name="Episode 2" />

Shortly after the battle had moved away from the arena, the famed Republic [[Clone commando/Legends|clone commandos]] of [[Delta Squad/Legends|Delta Squad]] fought their way into the High Audience Chamber, slaying the Geonosian [[Lieutenant/Legends|lieutenant]] [[Sun Fac/Legends|Sun Fac]] and shutting down the droid foundry beneath the arena. After the battle had been completely won, Republic forces took control of the planet, and droid remains were taken to be melted down.
